Date: Fri, Nov 9, 2012 at 12:11 AM<br>Subject: [CrisisMappers] Looking for 2 consultants for crisismap for agrarian conflict in Indonesia<br>To: <a href="mailto:crisismappers@...">crisismappers@...</a><br>

<br><br><div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent"><br></div><div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent">

We are working with local NGOs, with financial assistance from the Ford Foundation, to develop an online, open access system to map incidents of violent conflict between local communities and plantation companies in Indonesia.  Based on a Ushahidi and Frontline SMS platform, the system will also allow the public to submit reports, will monitor social media, and also collect relevant open source information from the web.</div>

<div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent"><br></div><div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent">

We are looking for 2 individuals able to identify<span style="font-family:Garamond;font-size:12pt"> creative, practical solutions for low bandwidth, non-smartphone environments.  We need</span><span style="background-color:transparent">:</span></div>

<div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent"><span style="background-color:transparent"><br></span></div><div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent">

1) <span style="font-weight:bold">A PROJECT MANAGER</span> to work with our Indonesian programmers, with experience designing and building mapping/database systems that use tools like Ushahidi and Frontline SMS and with knowledge of other available tools for monitoring and verifiying social media. </div>

<div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent"><span style="background-color:transparent"><br></span></div><div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent">

<span style="background-color:transparent">and </span></div><div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent"><span style="background-color:transparent"><br></span></div>

<div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent"><span style="background-color:transparent">2) <span style="font-weight:bold">A COMMUNITY OUTREACH MANAGER</span> with experience</span><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:Garamond"> engaging lay users in a cross-cultural environment to design and fine-tune the system so it is of optimal use to the users themselves and to encourage reporting.</span></span></div>

<div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:Garamond"><br></span></span></div><div style="font-family:garamond,&#39;new york&#39;,times,serif;font-size:16px;background-color:transparent">

